Load Data

# read in data, delete headers, and make working copy of data
Data_raw <- read.csv("./FullRawData/MITei Mobility Culture Survey - Singapore_April 16, 2019_14.12.csv", stringsAsFactors=FALSE)
Data_raw <- Data_raw[3:nrow(Data_raw),]  #remove extra header rows
Data_SG <- Data_raw

#Create simple function that reverses a 7-point Likert scale
flipscale <- function(x) {( 8 - x )}

Data Cleaning

### Cleaning sociodemographic variables
Data_SG <- Data_SG %>% mutate(DOB = as.numeric(as.character(Age)),
                              Age = 2019 - DOB,
                              Male = ifelse(Gender=="1", 1, 0),
                              Educ = as.numeric(Educ),
                              ColDeg = ifelse(Educ==5, 1, 0),
                              GradDeg = ifelse(Educ==6 | Educ==7, 1, 0),
                              BelowSecondary = ifelse(Educ==1, 1, 0),
                              Secondary = ifelse(Educ==2, 1, 0),
                              PostSecondary = ifelse(Educ==3, 1, 0),
                              Diploma = ifelse(Educ==4, 1, 0),
                              University = ifelse(Educ>4, 1, 0),
                              Employ = as.numeric(Employ),
                              Employed = ifelse(Employ==6 | Employ==7, 1, 0),
                              Student = ifelse(Employ==9, 1, 0),
                              HHPers = as.numeric(HHPers),
                              Kids = as.numeric(Kids),
                              Kids = ifelse(Kids>0, 1, 0),
                              HHInc = ifelse(HHInc=="19", NA, as.numeric(HHInc)),
                              HHCars = as.numeric(HHCars),
                              CarOwner = ifelse(HHCars > 1, 1, 0) #HHCars=1 indicates zero cars
                              )

Data_SG$HHCars <- car::recode(Data_SG$HHCars, "1=0; 2=1; 3=2; 4=3")

#HHInc: What is your household monthly income (including employer CPF contributions, if applicable) in Singapore dollars?
#1=Below $1000=500, 2=$1000-2499=1750, 3=$2500-3999=3250, 4=$4000-4999=4500, (no 5), 
#6=$5000-5999=5500, 7=$6000-6999=6500, 8=$7000-7999=7500, 9=$8000-8999=9500, 
#10=$9000-9999=9500, 11=$10000-10999=10500, 12=$11000-12999=12000, 13=$13000-14999=14000, 
#(no 14), 15=$15000-17499=16250, (no 16), 17=$17500-19999=18750, 18=$20000 or more=21250, 
#19(unknown)
Data_SG$HHInc <- car::recode(Data_SG$HHInc, 
                             "1=500; 2=1750; 3=3250; 4=4500; 6=5500; 7=6500;
                             8=7500; 9=8500; 10=9500; 11=10500; 12=12000; 
                             13=14000; 15=16250; 17=18750; 18=21250")
Data_SG$HHInc_yearly <- Data_SG$HHInc*12


#Q8. "What percentage of your monthly trips do you currently fulfill by each of the following modes? (trips can include, but are not limited to, any travel among home, work, school, shopping, food, recreation, healthcare or other social service/facility, etc.)"
#  _1 = Private/Personal car
#  _2 = Taxi
#  _3 = Ridehailing: private service (e.g. GrabCar Economy or Premium, Ryde, or GOJEK GOCAR)
#  _4 = Ridehailing: shared service (e.g. GrabShare or Ryde Carpool)
#  _5 = Motorcycle or scooter
#  _6 = MRT/LRT
#  _7 = Bus
#  _8 = Bicycle
#  _9 = Walk

#Based on share of travel by mode, categorize users by frequency of use. 
#  Combine bus and rail into PT; combine walk and bike into NMT.

Data_SG <- Data_SG %>% mutate(Car_Share = as.numeric(Q8_1),
                              Taxi_Share = as.numeric(Q8_2),
                              ERH_Share = as.numeric(Q8_3), #ERH = exclusive ride-hailing
                              PRH_Share = as.numeric(Q8_4), #PRH = pooled ride-hailing
                              RH_Share = ERH_Share + PRH_Share,
                              Fleet_Share = RH_Share + Taxi_Share, 
                              PT_Share = as.numeric(Q8_6) + as.numeric(Q8_7),
                              NMT_Share = as.numeric(Q8_8) + as.numeric(Q8_9),
                              NMT_SuperUser = ifelse(NMT_Share >= 20, 1, 0), #110 individuals
                              NMT_FreqUser = ifelse(NMT_Share %in% 10:19, 1, 0), #242 individuals
                              NMT_RegUser = ifelse(NMT_Share %in% 1:9, 1, 0), #214 individuals
                              NMT_NonUser = ifelse(NMT_Share < 1, 1, 0), #234 individuals
                              PT_SuperUser = ifelse(PT_Share >= 71, 1, 0),  #188 
                              PT_FreqUser = ifelse(PT_Share %in% 46:70, 1, 0), #205 
                              PT_RegUser = ifelse(PT_Share %in% 11:45, 1, 0), #231 
                              PT_LowUser = ifelse(PT_Share < 11, 1, 0), #176 
#cutoff based on summary statistics; only 71 individuals in the sample are non-users because Singapore is super transit-oriented
                              Car_SuperUser = ifelse(Car_Share >= 60, 1, 0),  #175 
                              Car_FreqUser = ifelse(Car_Share %in% 20:59, 1, 0), #192 
                              Car_RegUser = ifelse(Car_Share %in% 1:19, 1, 0), #147 
                              Car_NonUser = ifelse(Car_Share < 1, 1, 0), #286 
                              Taxi_FreqUser = ifelse(Taxi_Share >= 8, 1, 0), # 189 
                              Taxi_RegUser = ifelse(Taxi_Share %in% 1:7, 1, 0), #185 
                              Taxi_NonUser = ifelse(Taxi_Share < 1, 1, 0), #426 
                              RH_FreqUser = ifelse(RH_Share >= 20, 1, 0), #183 
                              RH_RegUser = ifelse(RH_Share %in% 1:19, 1, 0), #341 
                              RH_NonUser = ifelse(RH_Share < 1, 1, 0), #279 
                              Fleet_SuperUser = ifelse(Fleet_Share >= 30, 1, 0), #155 
                              Fleet_FreqUser = ifelse(Fleet_Share %in% 13:29, 1, 0), #200
                              Fleet_RegUser = ifelse(Fleet_Share %in% 1:12, 1, 0), #221 
                              Fleet_NonUser = ifelse(Fleet_Share < 1, 1, 0) #227 
                              ) 

#AV_Know    What is your current level of knowledge of autonomous vehicle technology?   1-I have no knowledge of autonomous vehicles, 2-I have little knowledge of autonomous vehicles (for example, I have heard of or seen them), 3-I have a moderate knowledge of autonomous vehicles (for example, I have read about them), 4-I have advanced knowledge of autonomous vehicles, 5-I am a developer of autonomous vehicle technology

#AV_Ride    Have you ever ridden in an autonomous vehicle?  1-Yes, 2-No

#AV_SafePerc    How safe do you think autonomous vehicle technology is today?   1-Very safe, 2-Somewhat safe, 3-Not very safe, 4-Not safe at all

#AV_SafePredict How soon, if at all, do you think autonomous vehicles will be safe enough for you to consider using one?    1-I would consider using one now, 2-Within the next 2 years, 3-In 2-5 years, 4-In 5-10 years, 5-In 10-20 years, 6-More than 20 years, 7-Never

Descriptive Statistics of Outcome Variables

Data processing

Data_SG <- Data_SG %>% mutate(PAV_Purch = flipscale(as.numeric(PAV_Purch_1)),
                              PAV_WTP = as.numeric(PAV_WTP),
                              PAV_WTP = ifelse(PAV_WTP > 1000000, 1000000, PAV_WTP),
                              PAV_Freq = as.numeric(PAV_Freq_1),
                              PrivFreqDiff = PAV_Freq - Car_Share,
                              SAV_IntendUse_1 = as.numeric(SAV_IntendUse_1), #for exclusive
                              SAV_IntendUse_2 = as.numeric(SAV_IntendUse_2), #for pooled
                              SAV_IntendUse_max = pmax(SAV_IntendUse_1, SAV_IntendUse_2),
                              SAV_IntendUse_mean = ((SAV_IntendUse_1 + SAV_IntendUse_2) / 2),
                              SAV_Freq_1 = as.numeric(SAV_Freq_1), #for exclusive
                              SAV_Freq_2 = as.numeric(SAV_Freq_2), #for pooled
                              SAV_Freq = SAV_Freq_1 + SAV_Freq_2,
                              SAV_Freq = ifelse(SAV_Freq > 100, 100, SAV_Freq),
                              FleetFreqDiff1 = SAV_Freq - RH_Share,
                              FleetFreqDiff2 = SAV_Freq - Fleet_Share,
                              SAV_HHCars = as.numeric(SAV_HHCars),
                              AV_IntendDiff = PAV_Purch - SAV_IntendUse_max
                              )

#Veh_Price_Used = "What was the purchase price of the vehicle (including the COE price, if applicable)?" (in Singaporean dollars)   
# (no 1-3)
#  4-Below S$10,000,        11-S$70,000-79,999, 
#  5-S$10,000-19,999,       12-S$80,000-89,999,
#  6-S$20,000-29,999,       13-S$90,000-99,999,
#  7-S$30,000-39,999,       14-S$100,000-149,999, (no 15)
#  8-S$40,000-49,999,       16-S$150,000-199,999,
#  9-S$50,000-59,999,       17-More than S$200,000
#  10-S$60,000-69,999,      18-N/A
Data_SG$Veh_Price_Used <- car::recode(Data_SG$Veh_Price_Used, 
                             "4=5000; 5=15000; 6=25000; 7=35000; 8=45000; 9=55000; 10=65000; 11=75000; 
                             12=85000; 13=95000; 14=125000; 16=175000; 17=225000; 18=18")

#Veh_Price_New = "What was the purchase price of the vehicle (including the COE price, if applicable)?" (in Singaporean dollars)
#  (no 1-3, 5, or 7)
#  4-Below S$50,000,        12-S$175,000-199,999,
#  6-S$50,000-74,999,       13-S$200,000-249,999,
#  8-S$75,000-99,999,       14-S$250,000-299,999, 
#  9-S$100,000-124,999,     15-S$300,000-$349,999,
#  10-S$125,000-149,999,    16-More than S$350,000,
#  11-S$150,000-174,999,    17-N/A
Data_SG$Veh_Price_New <- car::recode(Data_SG$Veh_Price_New, 
                             "4=25000; 6=62500; 8=87500; 9=112500; 10=137500; 11=162500; 
                              12=187500; 13=225000; 14=275000; 15=325000; 16=375000; 17=17")

Data_SG <- Data_SG %>% mutate(Veh_Price_Used = ifelse(Veh_Price_Used=="18" | Veh_Price_Used=="",NA, as.numeric(Veh_Price_Used)),
                              Veh_Price_New = ifelse((Veh_Price_New=="17" | Veh_Price_New==""),NA, as.numeric(Veh_Price_New)),
                              VehPrice = ifelse(Veh_Used==1, Veh_Price_Used, Veh_Price_New),
                              #Vehicle price as percentage of household yearly income
                              VehPrice_Inc = ((VehPrice / HHInc_yearly) * 100),
                              #Willingness to pay for private AV as percentage of vehicle price
                              WTP_VehPrice = ((PAV_WTP / VehPrice) * 100),
                              #Willingness to pay for private AV as percentage of household yearly income
                              WTP_Inc = ((PAV_WTP / HHInc_yearly) * 100)
                              )

PAV_Purch_1 = âIf completely autonomous vehicles were available today, how likely would you be to purchase one as your next vehicle?â (Likert scale: 1 = Extremely likely to 7 = Extremely unlikely)

SAV_IntendUse = âIf a completely autonomous mobility-on-demand service were available today, how likely would you be to use the private/exclusive serviceâ (Likert scale: 1 = Extremely likely to 7 = Extremely unlikely)

levels.7pt.likely <- c("Extremely unlikely", "Unlikely", "Slightly unlikely", "Neither likely nor unlikely", "Slightly likely",  "Likely", "Extremely likely")
Data_SG$PAV_Purch <- as.factor(as.character(Data_SG$PAV_Purch))

Measurement Model â UTAUT+ Latent Variables

See code at [insert URL] for details on measure development

grep("PerfExp_1", colnames(Data_SG)) #106
## [1] 106
grep("TechInt_8", colnames(Data_SG)) #145
## [1] 145
Data_SG[106:145] <- lapply(Data_SG[106:145], as.numeric)

# All survey items on Likert-scale from 1 = strongly agree to 7 = strongly disagree
#   No missing data
Data_SG[106:145] <- lapply(Data_SG[106:145], flipscale) #Flip so that higher value = agreement

#Final measurement model
CFA_final <- 'PerfExp =~ PerfExp_1 + PerfExp_2 + PerfExp_3 + PerfExp_4 + PerfExp_5 + PerfExp_7
             PerfExp_1 ~~ PerfExp_2
             EffExp =~ EffExp_1 + EffExp_2 + EffExp_3 + EffExp_6
             SocInf =~ SocInf_1 + SocInf_2 + SocInf_3
             FacCond =~ FacCond_2 + FacCond_3 + FacCond_4
             HedMotiv =~ HedMotiv_1 + HedMotiv_2 + HedMotiv_4
             Trust =~ Trust_1 + Trust_2 + Trust_3 + Trust_4 + Trust_5 + Trust_7
             Trust_2 ~~ Trust_5
             TechInt =~ TechInt_1 + TechInt_4 + TechInt_5 + TechInt_7 + TechInt_8
             TechInt_7 ~~ TechInt_8'
